          <msContents>
            <summary>Tables used in an astrological technique for determining auspicious times for carrying out various activities. Also includes geographical illustrations and diagrams and half of a horoscope diagram for a location in northern Afghanistan dated Friday, 27 Shawwāl 912 (12 March 1507).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Jadāvil-i ikhtiyārāt.</title>
              <title type="vernacular">[جداول اختيارات]</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>former owner</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Schoenberg, Lawrence J</persName>
              </respStmt>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc material="mixed">
                <support>
                  <p>paper</p>
                </support>
                <extent>7 leaves : 216 x 137 (145 x 109) mm. bound to 220 x 144 mm</extent>
                <foliation>Paper, 7; [1-7]; modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto.</foliation>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout>Textblock border-ruled in gold with vertical margins extended to upper edge of the page.</layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <scriptDesc>
              <scriptNote>Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed, with headings in naskh script.</scriptNote>
            </scriptDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote>6 colored diagrams (eastern half of a double-page world map, f. 1r; structure and arrangement of seven climatic zones, f. 2v; geographical relationship of various cities to Mecca, f. 3r; rainbow predictions, f. 4v; setting and rising of the moon, f. 5r; half of a double-page horoscope diagram, f. 7v) and 8 decorated tables (ikhtiyārāt for the days of the solar month, f. 1v-2r; ikhtiyārāt for the lunar mansions, f. 3v-4r; ikhtiyārāt for the moon in one of the zodiacal signs, f. 5v-6r); marginal ruling in gold; significant words or numbers in red or green ink.</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="1r">Diagram, Eastern half of world map, f. 1r</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="2v">Diagram, Seven climatic zones, f. 2v</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="3r">Diagram, Geographical relationship of various cities to Mecca, f. 3r</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="4v">Diagram, Rainbow predictions, f. 4v</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="5r">Diagram, Setting and rising of the moon, f. 5r</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="7v">Diagram, Half of a horoscope diagram, f. 7v</decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
            <bindingDesc>
              <binding>
                <p>19th-century light brown leather with faded, gold-tooled frame.</p>
              </binding>
            </bindingDesc>
          </physDesc>
          <history>
            <origin>
              <p>Written in the Timurid Empire in eastern Persia, now Iran, ca. 1507 (based on date of horoscope diagram, f. 7v).</p>
              <origDate>approximately A.H. 912 (1507)</origDate>
              <origPlace>Iran?</origPlace>
            </origin>
            <provenance>Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Mar. 2002.</provenance>
            <provenance>Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.</provenance>
            <provenance>Gift of Barbara Brizdle Schoenberg, 2016.</provenance>
          </history>
